{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17496480","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17496480"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T08:48:06+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T08:48:06+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1367"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17582911","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17582911"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:00:16+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:00:16+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1367"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1367","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1367"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.1,0.05,0.5,0.24,0.12]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1367"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96858"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1367","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1367"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1367"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79473"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"35"},{"type":"tags","id":"41"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"723"},{"type":"tags","id":"1181"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5743"},{"type":"contributions","id":"9113"},{"type":"contributions","id":"15981"},{"type":"contributions","id":"33150"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96858","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/96858"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 59-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a 12-month history of painless swelling in front of his left ear. He has not experienced any recent illness, weight loss, night sweats, or fever. He denies facial weakness, difficulty opening his mouth, or problems with eating. His medical history includes hypertension, controlled with perindopril. He has a 20-pack year smoking history and consumes one standard drink of alcohol daily.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. There is a 3 cm firm, mobile, non-tender swelling anterior to the left ear and superficial to the angle of the mandible (Image). There is no cervical lymphadenopathy. Facial nerve function is intact bilaterally.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following anatomical structures does this swelling most likely arise from?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Anterior cervical lymph node","Sternocleidomastoid muscle","Parotid gland","Submandibular gland","Branchial cleft cyst"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe swelling in this case most likely arises from the \u003Cstrong\u003Eparotid gland\u003C/strong\u003E. The parotid gland is located in the preauricular region, superficial to the mandibular ramus. It is bordered by the zygomatic arch superiorly, the external ear and sternocleidomastoid muscle posteriorly, and the masseter muscle anteriorly. The facial nerve courses through the substance of the parotid gland, dividing it into superficial and deep lobes. The clinical presentation of a painless, slow-growing swelling in this region over 12 months is characteristic of a pleomorphic adenoma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior cervical lymph nodes\u003C/strong\u003E are located in the anterior triangle of the neck, which is formed by the midline, the anterior border of the sternocleidomastoid muscle, and the inferior border of the mandible. Lymphadenopathy would typically be more inferior and medial than this presentation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esternocleidomastoid muscle\u003C/strong\u003E lies posterior to the parotid gland. A mass arising from this muscle would be more posterior and would likely affect neck movement, which is not present in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esubmandibular gland\u003C/strong\u003E lies within the submandibular triangle, inferior to the mandible. A swelling arising from this gland would be located below the angle of the jaw, not anterior to the ear as described.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Ebranchial cleft cyst\u003C/strong\u003E typically presents as a smooth, round mass along the anterior border of the sternocleidomastoid muscle. While it can present in adults, it is more commonly diagnosed in childhood or early adulthood and would be located more inferiorly in the neck.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The parotid gland is located superficial to the mandibular ramus and anterior to the ear.","Painless, slow-growing swelling in the parotid region is characteristic of a pleomorphic adenoma.","The facial nerve courses through the parotid gland, dividing it into superficial and deep lobes."],"references":["Kikuta S, Iwanaga J, Kusukawa J, Tubbs RS. Triangles of the neck: a review with clinical/surgical applications. Anat Cell Biol. 2019 Jun;52(2):120-127. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31338227/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79473"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1367"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"19988"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"19988","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/19988"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/c9edcf84-5cf8-4c47-9c11-94cc440c0b0b.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/c9edcf84-5cf8-4c47-9c11-94cc440c0b0b.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":587,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79473","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/79473"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-04-03T08:52:46+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-03T08:54:02+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1367"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96858"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"35","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/35"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc43","name":"Otorhinolaryngology","synonyms":["ENT","HEENT"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:40:48+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"41","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/41"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc80","name":"Anatomy","synonyms":null,"descri